6}, {\"ngram\": \"two straights\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"two 180-degree circular bends\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First constructed during the 19thcentury, sizes used to vary, but since 1990 most major events in the sport are held on 250 metre tracks.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \", sizes\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1448}, {\"ngram\": \"most major events\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1495}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"250 metre tracks\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of the track cycling will be held at the Velodrome National de Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines just west of Paris, a venue that has twice hosted the World Championships.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0088384679622945e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the track cycling\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1564}, {\"ngram\": \"the Velodrome National de Saint-Quentin-en\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"Yvelines\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"a venue\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The omnium was streamlined ahead of the last Olympics, and will again be held over one day and four events in Paris - down from the two-day, six event competition in Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1875, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6372603680329963e-17, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The omnium\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"the last Olympics\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"one day\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"four events\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"the two-day, six event competition\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four separate bunch events are: the scratch race, the tempo race, the elimination race and the points race.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 2003, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The four separate bunch events\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1922}, {\"ngram\": \"the scratch race\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1944}, {\"ngram\": \"the tempo race\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the elimination race\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Riders accumulate points in the first three events based on a points scale, which are then carried in to the points race.\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Riders\", \"from\": 2005, \"to\": 2011}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"the first three events\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"a points scale\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"the points race\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the course of this race riders may lose or gain points from their total, and the winner is the rider with the most points at the end of the fourth event, which is 25km for men and 20km for women.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2144}, {\"ngram\": \"this race riders\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 2182, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"their total\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\